Murphy Television\n*[[20th Century Fox Television]]\n}}\n| distributor              = [[20th Television]]<br>[[20th Century Fox Television Distribution]]<ref>{{Cite web|title=Sky UK among buyers of Ryan Murphy's Fox drama 9-1-1|url=https://tbivision.com/2018/03/05/sky-uk-among-buyers-of-ryan-murphys-fox-drama-9-1-1/|work=TBI Vision|date=March 5, 2018}}</ref>\n| network                  = [[Fox Broadcasting Company|Fox]]\n| picture_format           = [[1080i]] ([[High-definition television|HDTV]])\n| audio_format             = \n| first_aired              = {{Start date|2018|1|3}}\n| last_aired               = {{End date|present}}\n| related                  = ''[[9-1-1: Lone Star]]''\n| website                  = https://www.fox.com/9-1-1/\n| production_website       = \n}}\n'''''9-1-1''''' is an American [[Procedural (genre)|procedural]] [[television series]] created by [[Ryan Murphy (writer)|Ryan Murphy]],<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.eonline.com/news/890026/your-first-look-at-ryan-murphy-s-9-1-1-is-here|title=Your First Look at Ryan Murphy's 9-1-1 Is Here|date=October 27, 2017|work=E! Online|accessdate=September 25, 2018}}</ref> [[Brad Falchuk]] and [[Tim Minear]] for the [[Fox Broadcasting Company]]. The series follows the lives of Los Angeles [[first responder]]s: [[police officer]]s, [[paramedic]]s, [[firefighter]]s and [[Radio dispatcher|dispatcher]]s. \n\nThe series premiered on January 3, 2018.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://deadline.com/2017/11/x-files-9-1-1-fox-premiere-dates-1202209051/|title='The X-Files' & New Drama '9-1-1' Get Premiere Dates On Fox|last=Evans|first=Greg|date=November 15, 2017|website=[[Deadline Hollywood]]|access-date=November 16, 2017}}</ref><ref name=deadline1>{{cite web|url=https://deadline.com/2017/05/fox-schedule-primetime-fall-2017-2018-the-gifted-empire-the-exorcist-1202093477/|title=Fox Fall 2017 Schedule: 'Empire' Shifts to 8 PM, 'Gotham' Moves to Thursday, 'Lethal Weapon' to Tuesday|website=Deadline Hollywood|date=May 15, 2017|first=Nellie|last=Andreeva}}</ref>  ''9-1-1'' is a joint production between Reamworks, Ryan Murphy Television, and [[20th Century Fox Television]] and syndicated by [[20th Television]]. In March 2019, Fox renewed the series for a third season which premiered on September 23, 2019.<ref name=\"S3Renewal\"/><ref name=\"S3PremiereDate\"/> In April 2020, Fox renewed the series for a fourth season.<ref name=\"S4Renewal\"/>\n\nIn May 2019, Fox ordered a spin-off series titled ''[[9-1-1: Lone Star]]''; starring [[Rob Lowe]] and [[Liv Tyler]], which premiered on January 19, 2020.<ref name=\"LoneStar\">{{cite web|last1=Lannuci|first1=Rebecca|title=9-1-1 Spinoff Lone Star Scores Series Order at Fox, Rob Lowe to Star|url=https://tvline.com/2019/05/12/9-1-1-spinoff-series-order-fox-rob-lowe-lone-star/|website=[[TVLine]]|accessdate=May 13, 2019|date=May 12, 2019}}</ref><ref name=adweek-Lynch>{{cite magazine|last=Lynch|first=Jason|date=May 13, 2019|title=Fox Brings Back The Masked Singer This Fall, Then Will Debut Season 3 After Super Bowl LIV|url=https://www.adweek.com/tv-video/fox-brings-back-the-masked-singer-this-fall-then-will-debut-season-3-after-super-bowl-liv/|magazine=[[Adweek]]|access-date=October 1, 2019}}</ref>\n\n==Cast and characters==\n{{Main|List of 9-1-1 characters}}\n*[[Angela Bassett]] as Athena Carter Grant Nash, [[Los Angeles Police Department|LAPD]] patrol sergeant\n*[[Peter Krause]] as Robert \"Bobby\" Nash, [[Los Angeles Fire Department|LAFD]] Station 118 captain and Athena's second husband\n*[[Oliver Stark]] as Evan \"Buck\" Buckley, firefighter\n*[[Aisha Hinds]] as Henrietta \"Hen\" Wilson, firefighter/paramedic\n*[[Kenneth Choi]] as Howard \"Howie\"/\"Chimney\" Han, firefighter/paramedic\n*[[Rockmond Dunbar]] as Michael Grant, Athena's ex-husband\n*[[Connie Britton]] as Abigail \"Abby\" Clark, 911 operator (season 1; recurring season 3)<ref>{{cite web|url=https://tvline.com/2020/01/21/911-connie-britton-return-explained-buck-reunion/|title=9-1-1 EP Teases Connie Britton's Return, Abby's 'Unfinished Business' With Buck|date=January 21, 2020|access-date=March 4, 2020|work=TVLine}}</ref>\n*[[Jennifer Love Hewitt]] as Madeline \"Maddie\" Buckley Kendall,<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.fox.com/9-1-1/credits/5b739cbd5d20f8001bca212a/|title=Meet the Cast: Jennifer Love Hewitt as Maddie Kendall|website=[[Fox (channel)|FOX]]|access-date=August 30, 2018}}</ref> 911 operator, Buck's sister, and Chimney's girlfriend. (season 2 \u2013 present)<ref name=\"JLHSeason2\">{{cite web|url=https://ew.com/tv/2018/05/14/9-1-1-jennifer-love-hewitt-season-2/|title=9-1-1 adds Jennifer Love Hewitt for season 2|last=Abrams|first=Natalie|date=May 14, 2018|website=[[Entertainment Weekly]]|access-date=May 14, 2018}}</ref>\n*[[Ryan Guzman]] as Edmundo \"Eddie\" Diaz, firefighter (season 2 \u2013 present)<ref name=\"RGSeason2\">{{cite web|last=Pederson|first=Erik|date=May 23, 2018|title='9-1-1': Ryan Guzman Joins Fox Drama as Firefighter|url=https://deadline.com/2018/05/9-1-1-ryan-guzman-joins-fox-drama-as-firefighter-1202397081/|website=[[Deadline Hollywood]]|access-date=May 23, 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.fox.com/9-1-1/credits/5b739e3e5d20f8001bca2132/|title=Meet the Cast: Ryan Guzman as Eddie Diaz|website=[[Fox (channel)|FOX]]|access-date=August 17, 2018}}</ref>\n*Corinne Massiah as May Grant, Athena and Michael's daughter (recurring season 1; season 2 \u2013 present)<ref name=\"GrantKidsSeason2\">{{cite web|last=Pederson|first=Erik|date=June 4, 2018|title='9-1-1': Corinne Massiah & Marcanthonee Reis Upped To Series Regulars for Season 2 of Fox Drama|url=https://deadline.com/2018/06/9-1-1-season-2-corinne-massiah-marcanthonee-reis-angela-bassett-ryan-murphy-fox-1202403220/|website=[[Deadline Hollywood]]|access-date=June 4, 2018}}</ref>\n*Marcanthonee Jon Reis as Harry Grant, Athena and Michael's son (recurring season 1; season 2 \u2013 present)<ref name=\"GrantKidsSeason2\" />\n*Gavin McHugh as Christopher Diaz, Eddie's son (recurring season 2; main season 3)<ref>{{cite web|title=(#NIN-303) 'The Searchers'|url=http://www.thefutoncritic.com/listings/20190919fox02/|publisher=[[The Futon Critic]]|accessdate=September 19, 2019}}</ref>\n\n==Episodes==\n{{Main|List of 9-1-1 episodes}}\n{{:List of 9-1-1 episodes}}\n\n==Production==\n===Development===\nThe series is produced by [[20th Century Fox Television]], with Murphy, Falchuk, Minear and [[Bradley Buecker]] as [[executive producer]]s. Minear also serves as [[showrunner]] and Buecker [[Film director|directed]] the premiere episode.<ref name=\"deadline2\">{{cite web|url=https://deadline.com/2017/10/9-1-1-connie-britton-star-ryan-murphy-brad-falchuk-fox-series-1202181179/|title='9-1-1': Connie Britton To Star In Ryan Murphy & Brad Falchuk's Fox Series|last=Andreeva|first=Nellie|date=October 3, 2017|website=Deadline Hollywood|access-date=November 16, 2017}}</ref> On January 16, 2018, Fox renewed the series for an eighteen-episode second season.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://tvline.com/2018/01/16/911-renewed-for-season-2-at-fox/|title=9-1-1 Renewed for Season 2 at Fox|last=Ausiello|first=Michael|date=January 16, 2018|website=[[TVLine]]|access-date=January 16, 2018}}</ref><ref name=\"eighteen\">{{cite web|url=https://deadline.com/2018/10/fox-midseason-premiere-dates-gotham-final-season-proven-innocent-the-orville-the-passage-1202491542/|title=Fox Sets More Midseason Premiere Dates: 'Gotham' Final Season, 'Orville' Return, 'The Passage' & 'Proven Innocent', More|last=Andreeva|first=Nellie|date=October 29, 2018|website=Deadline Hollywood|access-date=October 31, 2018}}</ref> The second season premiered with a special episode on Sunday, September 23, 2018, at 8 p.m. EDT; the second episode aired in the series's regular 9 p.m. EDT time slot on Monday, September 24, 2018.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.eonline.com/news/947811/fox-reveals-2018-fall-tv-premiere-dates-find-out-when-9-1-1-last-man-standing-and-more-return|title=Fox Reveals 2018 Fall TV Premiere Dates: Find Out When 9-1-1, Last Man Standing and More Return|last=Harnick|first=Chris|date=June 28, 2018|website=Eonline|accessdate=September 14, 2018}}</ref>  On March 25, 2019, Fox renewed the series for a third season which is set to premiere on September 23, 2019.<ref name=\"S3Renewal\">{{cite web|url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/live-feed/911-resident-renewed-at-fox-2019-20-1196818|title='911,' 'The Resident' Renewed at Fox|work=The Hollywood Reporter|first1=Rick|last1=Porter|first2=Lesley|last2=Goldberg|date=March 25, 2019|accessdate=March 25, 2019}}</ref><ref name=\"S3PremiereDate\">{{cite web|url=https://deadline.com/2019/08/9-1-1-ronda-rousey-to-recur-in-season-3-of-foxs-first-responders-drama-1202669025/|title='9-1-1': Ronda Rousey To Recur In Season 3 with 4 episodes Of Fox's First-Responders Drama|work=Deadline Hollywood|first=Denise|last=Petski|date=August 15, 2019|accessdate=August 17, 2019}}</ref> On April 13, 2020, Fox renewed the series for a fourth season.<ref name=\"S4Renewal\">{{cite web|url=https://deadline.com/2020/04/9-1-1-9-1-1-lone-star-renewed-season-4-fox-ryan-murphy-2020-21-1202900985/|title='9-1-1' & Spinoff '9-1-1: Lone Star' Renewed By Fox For 2020-21 Season|work=Deadline Hollywood|first=Denise|last=Petski|date=April 13, 2020|accessdate=April 13, 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200413220303/https://deadline.com/2020/04/9-1-1-9-1-1-lone-star-renewed-season-4-fox-ryan-murphy-2020-21-1202900985/|archive-date=April 13, 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n===Casting===\nIn October 2017, [[Connie Britton]], [[Angela Bassett]], and [[Peter Krause]] joined the main cast.<ref name=\"deadline2\"/> Later that month, it was announced that [[Oliver Stark]], [[Aisha Hinds]], [[Kenneth Choi]], and [[Rockmond Dunbar]] had been cast in regular roles.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://variety.com/2017/tv/news/9-1-1-fox-ryan-murphy-aisha-hinds-rockmond-dunbar-oliver-stark-kenneth-choi-1202588481/|title=Ryan Murphy's '9-1-1' Adds Four to Cast, Including Rockmond Dunbar, Aisha Hinds|last=Otterson|first=Joe|date=October 12, 2017|website=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]]|access-date=November 16, 2017}}</ref>\n\nOn May 14, 2018, it was announced that [[Jennifer Love Hewitt]] would join the main cast in season 2, replacing Britton, as Maddie Buckley, Buck's sister and the new 9-1-1 operator.<ref name=\"JLHSeason2\"/> On May 23, 2018, Fox announced that [[Ryan Guzman]] would be joining the second season of the series as new firefighter Eddie Diaz.<ref name=\"RGSeason2\"/> On June 4, 2018, it was announced that Corinne Massiah and Marcanthonnee Jon Reis, who play May and Harry Grant, had been promoted, from their recurring roles in season 1, to series regulars for season 2.<ref name=\"GrantKidsSeason2\"/> Gavin McHugh, who plays Eddie's son Christopher, was promoted to a series regular in Season 3, after recurring in Season 2.\n\n==Reception==\n\n===Ratings===\n{{Television season ratings\n| hide_18_49_rating = y\n\n| link1             = List of 9-1-1 episodes#Season 1 (2018)\n| episodes1         = 10\n| timeslot1         = Wednesday 9:00&nbsp;pm\n| start1            = {{Start date|2018|1|3}}\n| startrating1      = 6.83<ref name=\"1.01\">{{cite web|url=http://tvbythenumbers.zap2it.com/daily-ratings/wednesday-final-ratings-jan-3-2018|title='Chicago PD' adjusts up, 'The X-Files' adjusts down: Wednesday final ratings|work=[[TV by the Numbers]]|first=Rick|last=Porter|date=January 5, 2018|accessdate=January 5, 2018}}</ref>\n| end1              = {{End date|2018|3|21}}\n| endrating1        = 6.63<ref name=\"1.10\">{{cite web|url=http://tvbythenumbers.zap2it.com/daily-ratings/wednesday-final-ratings-march-21-2018/|title='Survivor,' 'The Goldbergs' and 'Modern Family' adjust up, 'Speechless' adjusts down: Wednesday final ratings|work=TV by the Numbers|last=Porter|first=Rick|date=March 22, 2018|accessdate=March 22, 2018}}</ref>\n| season1           = 2017\u201318\n| rank1             = 21\n| viewers1          = 10.74<ref n