y 8:00&nbsp;pm\n| timeslot_length3  =\n| start3            = {{Start date|2019|9|23}}\n| startrating3      = 7.14<ref name=\"3.01\">{{cite web|url=https://tvbythenumbers.zap2it.com/daily-ratings/monday-final-ratings-september-23-2019/|title='9-1-1' and 'Bob Hearts Abishola' adjust up: Monday final ratings|work=TV by the Numbers|last=Rejent|first=Joseph|date=September 24, 2019|accessdate=September 24, 2019}}</ref>\n| end3              =\n| endrating3        =\n| season3           = 2019\u201320\n| rank3             =\n| viewers3          = \n}}\n\n===Critical response===\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders\" style=\"float: right;text-align:center; width:%70;margin:10px\"\n|-\n! style=\"padding:0 8px;\" colspan=\"2\" rowspan=\"2\"| Season\n! style=\"padding:0 8px;\" colspan=\"2\"| Critical response\n|-\n! style=\"padding:0 8px;\"| [[Rotten Tomatoes]]\n! style=\"padding:0 8px;\"| [[Metacritic]]\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" style=\"width:12px; background:#B7DFCD;\"|\n| 1\n| 70% (33 reviews)\n| 60% (22 critics)\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" style=\"width:12px; background:#242227;\"|\n| 2\n| 100% (7 reviews)\n| {{N/A}}\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" style=\"width:12px; background:#2B3F68;\"|\n| 3\n| 75% (8 reviews)\n| {{N/A}}\n|-\n|}\n\nThe [[review aggregator]] web site [[Rotten Tomatoes]] reported a 70% approval rating for the first season, based on 33 reviews, with an average rating of 5.86/10. The website's critical consensus reads, \"''9-1-1'' occasionally veers into melodrama, but is redeemed with a top-tier cast, adrenaline-pumping action, and a dash of trashy camp that pushes the show into addictive guilty pleasure territory.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.rottentomatoes.com/tv/9_1_1/s01|title=''9-1-1'': Season 1 (2018)|website=[[Rotten Tomatoes]]|accessdate=January 16, 2019}}</ref> [[Metacritic]], which uses a weighted average, assigned a score of 60 out of 100 based on 22 critics, indicating \"mixed or average reviews\".<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.metacritic.com/tv/9-1-1|title=''9-1-1'' (2018): Season 1 reviews|website=[[Metacritic]]|accessdate=January 16, 2019}}</ref>\n\nOn Rotten Tomatoes, the second season has an approval rating of 100%, based on 7 reviews, with an average rating of 7.75/10.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.rottentomatoes.com/tv/9_1_1/s02|title=''9-1-1'': Season 2 (2018)|website=[[Rotten Tomatoes]]|accessdate=January 16, 2019}}</ref>\n\n===Accolades===\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! Year\n! Award\n! Category\n! Nominee\n! Result\n! Ref.\n|-\n\n| rowspan=\"3\"|2018\n| [[BET Awards 2018|BET Awards]]\n| Best Actress\n| [[Angela Bassett]]\n| {{nom}}\n|{{Cn|date=May 2019}}\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\"|[[2018 Teen Choice Awards|Teen Choice Awards]]\n| [[Teen Choice Award for Choice Breakout Series|Choice Breakout TV Show]]\n| ''9-1-1''\n| rowspan=\"2\" {{nominated}}\n| rowspan=\"2\"|<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.etonline.com/teen-choice-awards-2018-the-complete-winners-list-107721|title=Teen Choice Awards 2018: The Complete Winners List|date=August 12, 2018|accessdate=August 12, 2018|work=[[Entertainment Tonight]]}}</ref>\n|-\n| Choice Breakout TV Star\n| rowspan=2| [[Oliver Stark]]\n|-\n|rowspan=2|2019\n|[[2019 Teen Choice Awards|Teen Choice Awards]]\n|Choice Drama TV Actor\n| {{nom}}\n|\n|-\n|Young Entertainer Awards\n|Best Guest Young Actor in an Television Series\n|Connor Dean\n|{{nom}}\n|{{Cn|date=May 2019}}\n|-\n| 2020\n| [[51st NAACP Image Awards|NAACP Image Awards]]\n| Outstanding Actress in a Drama Series\n| Angela Bassett\n| {{won}}\n|\n|}\n\n==Spin-off==\n{{Main|9-1-1: Lone Star}}\nOn May 12, 2019, it was announced that a spin-off, titled [[9-1-1: Lone Star]], will premiere on January 19, 2020 immediately following the NFC Championship game and continue the following night, January 20, 2020.<ref name=adweek-Lynch/> On the same day, [[Rob Lowe]] was announced to star.<ref>{{cite web|last=Andreeva|first=Nellie|date=May 12, 2019|url=https://deadline.com/2019/05/9-1-1-spinoff-rob-lowe-star-9-1-1-lone-star-fox-series-1202610804/|title='9-1-1' Spinoff Starring Rob Lowe Ordered By Fox; New Series '9-1-1: Lone Star' Will Premiere Next Season|website=[[Deadline Hollywood]]|access-date=October 1, 2019}}</ref> In September, [[Liv Tyler]],<ref>{{Cite web|last1=Andreeva|first1=Nellie|last2=Petski|first2=Denise|last-author-amp=yes|date=September 11, 2019|title=Liv Tyler Set as the Female Lead of Fox's '9-1-1: Lone Star' Spinoff Series|url=https://deadline.com/2019/09/liv-tyler-star-female-lead-fox-9-1-1-lone-star-spinoff-rob-lowe-1202731865/|website=[[Deadline Hollywood]]|access-date=October 1, 2019}}</ref> Ronen Rubinstein, Sierra McClain,<ref>{{Cite web|last1=Andreeva|first1=Nellie|last2=Petski|first2=Denise|last-author-amp=yes|date=September 20, 2019|title='9-1-1: Lone Star': Ronen Rubinstein & Sierra McClain Land Leads in Fox's Spinoff Series|url=https://deadline.com/2019/09/9-1-1-lone-star-ronen-rubinstein-sierra-mcclain-land-leads-in-foxs-spinoff-series-1202739517/|website=[[Deadline Hollywood]]|access-date=October 1, 2019}}</ref> [[Jim Parrack]],<ref>{{Cite web|last=Andreeva|first=Nellie|date=September 18, 2019|title='9-1-1: Lone Star: Jim Parrack Cast in Fox Spinoff Series|url=https://deadline.com/2019/09/9-1-1-lone-star-jim-parrack-cast-fox-spinoff-series-1202738287/|website=[[Deadline Hollywood]]|access-date=October 1, 2019}}</ref> Natacha Karam, [[Brian Michael Smith]], Julian Works, and Rafael Silva<ref>{{Cite web|last1=Andreeva|first1=Nellie|last2=Petski|first2=Denise|last-author-amp=yes|date=September 23, 2019|title='9-1-1: Lone Star': Natacha Karam & Brian Michael Smith Among 4 Cast in Fox Spinoff Series|url=https://deadline.com/2019/09/9-1-1-lone-star-natacha-karam-brian-michael-smith-rafael-silva-julian-works-fox-1202742827/|website=[[Deadline Hollywood]]|access-date=October 1, 2019}}</ref> were also announced to star in the series alongside Lowe.\n\n==Notes==\n{{notelist}}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist|30em}}\n\n==External links==\n*{{Official website}}\n*{{IMDb title|7235466}}\n\n{