e [[review aggregator]] web site [[Rotten Tomatoes]] reported a 70% approval rating for the first season, based on 33 reviews, with an average rating of 5.86/10. The website's critical consensus reads, \"''9-1-1'' occasionally veers into melodrama, but is redeemed with a top-tier cast, adrenaline-pumping action, and a dash of trashy camp that pushes the show into addictive guilty pleasure territory.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.rottentomatoes.com/tv/9_1_1/s01|title=''9-1-1'': Season 1 (2018)|website=[[Rotten Tomatoes]]|accessdate=January 16, 2019}}</ref> [[Metacritic]], which uses a weighted average, assigned a score of 60 out of 100 based on 22 critics, indicating \"mixed or average reviews\".<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.metacritic.com/tv/9-1-1|title=''9-1-1'' (2018): Season 1 reviews|website=[[Metacritic]]|accessdate=January 16, 2019}}</ref>\n\nOn Rotten Tomatoes, the second season has an approval rating of 100%, based on 7 reviews, with an average rating of 7.75/10.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.rottentomatoes.com/tv/9_1_1/s02|title=''9-1-1'': Season 2 (2018)|website=[[Rotten Tomatoes]]|accessdate=January 16, 2019}}</ref>\n\n===Accolades===\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! Year\n! Award\n! Category\n! Nominee\n! Result\n! Ref.\n|-\n\n| rowspan=\"3\"|2018\n| [[BET Awards 2018|BET Awards]]\n| Best Actress\n| [[Angela Bassett]]\n| {{nom}}\n|{{Cn|date=May 2019}}\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\"|[[2018 Teen Choice Awards|Teen Choice Awards]]\n| [[Teen Choice Award for Choice Breakout Series|Choice Breakout TV Show]]\n| ''9-1-1''\n| rowspan=\"2\" {{nominated}}\n| rowspan=\"2\"|<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.etonline.com/teen-choice-awards-2018-the-complete-winners-list-107721|title=Teen Choice Awards 2018: The Complete Winners List|date=August 12, 2018|accessdate=August 12, 2018|work=[[Entertainment Tonight]]}}</ref>\n|-\n| Choice Breakout TV Star\n| rowspan=2| [[Oliver Stark]]\n|-\n|rowspan=2|2019\n|[[2019 Teen Choice Awards|Teen Choice Awards]]\n|Choice Drama TV Actor\n| 